#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Combination Sum (Unlimited Use of Elements)

Is question mein hume combinations find karni hain jinka sum = target ho.
Important baat: Ek element ko hum multiple times use kar sakte hain.

Example:
candidates = [2,3,6,7], target = 7
Answer:
[2,2,3]
[7]

--------------------------------------------------
Main Idea
--------------------------------------------------
Har index par humare paas 2 choices hoti hain:

1. Pick karo element
   -> target se minus hoga
   -> index same rahega (kyuki same element dubara use kar sakte hain)

2. Not pick karo element
   -> index + 1 pe move karenge

Ye hi main logic hai.

--------------------------------------------------
Helper Function Meaning
--------------------------------------------------
helper(candidates, target, ans, idx, curr)

candidates = given array
target = remaining target
ans = final answer list
idx = current index
curr = current combination

--------------------------------------------------
Base Case
--------------------------------------------------
if(idx == candidates.length)
    Agar target == 0
        -> valid combination mil gaya
        -> curr ko answer me add karo
    return

Yaha recursion tab rukta hai jab array khatam ho jata hai.

--------------------------------------------------
Pick Condition
--------------------------------------------------
Hum element tabhi pick kar sakte hain
jab candidates[idx] <= target ho

curr.add(candidates[idx])
helper(candidates, target - candidates[idx], ans, idx, curr)
curr.remove(last)   // backtracking

Dhyaan do:
idx same pass ho raha hai
Kyuki same element unlimited times use kar sakte hain.

--------------------------------------------------
Not Pick Condition
--------------------------------------------------
helper(candidates, target, ans, idx+1, curr)

Yaha hum next element pe move kar rahe hain.

--------------------------------------------------
Recursion Tree Example
--------------------------------------------------
candidates = [2,3,5], target = 8

Start:
Take 2 → target = 6
Take 2 → target = 4
Take 2 → target = 2
Take 2 → target = 0 → [2,2,2,2]

Backtrack → try 3
2,3,3 → target = 0

Backtrack → try 5
3,5 → target = 0

--------------------------------------------------
Why duplicates nahi aate?
--------------------------------------------------
Kyuki hum index ko peeche nahi le ja rahe.
Hum sirf:
- same index (pick)
- next index (not pick)
Isliye same combination different order me nahi banegi.

--------------------------------------------------
Time Complexity
--------------------------------------------------
Exponential
Approx O(2^target)

--------------------------------------------------
Space Complexity
--------------------------------------------------
Recursion stack + combination list ≈ O(target)

--------------------------------------------------
One line intuition
--------------------------------------------------
Element ko pick karo (same index par raho) ya skip karo (next index par jao),
aur jab target 0 ho jaye to combination mil gayi.

